{"questionId":"9073152","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The air in a kitchen has pressure 1.0 × 10<sup>5</sup> Pa and temperature 22°C. A refrigerator of internal volume 0.36 m<sup>3</sup> is installed in the kitchen.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The refrigerator door is closed. The air in the refrigerator is cooled to 5.0°C and the number of air molecules in the refrigerator stays the same.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the pressure of the air inside the refrigerator.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>p</mi><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math> = constant&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>OR&nbsp;</strong></em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>OR&nbsp;</strong></em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>k</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math> ✔<br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math>« Pa »✔</span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE: Allow ECF from (a) <br>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for bald correct answer</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073152","referenceCode":"19N.2.SL.TZ0.b(i)","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the pressure of the air inside the refrigerator.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.2 – Modelling a gas","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"sche